{
  "texts": [
    "We can relate the deformation data defined above to the parallel transport in the Stokes local system along distinguished paths on Σ(Θ) as follows: Given a Stokes arrow, it determines two sectors π f (I) and π g (J) on ∂, where the corresponding real parts of the exponents are positive and negative, respectively.",
    "We can connect their midpoints by a path in Σ(Θ).",
    "Parallel transport along this path in the local system gives an isomorphism of stalks",
    "Pre-and post-composing this with the inclusion ι I and projection π J associated to the ⟨f ⟩-and ⟨g⟩-graded pieces, respectively, yields the deformation datum from Definition 4.9.",
    "In what follows, we will illustrate this by a path as drawn in Figure 5."
  ]
}